<item>
            <title>[LU-12445] Kernel &gt;= 4.19 have no *opened argument in atomic_open</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12445</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Since 4.19 or newer call iop-&amp;gt;atomic_open has no &lt;em&gt;*opened&lt;/em&gt; argument, &lt;br/&gt;
see &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/torvalds/linux/commit/a66b4cd1e7163adb327838a3c81faaf6a9330d5a&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;a66b4cd1e7163adb327838a3c81faaf6a9330d5a&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
namei.c:1049:15: error: &#8216;FILE_CREATED&#8217; undeclared (first use in &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; function); did you mean &#8216;FLD_CREATE&#8217;?
    *opened |= FILE_CREATED;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
</description>
                <environment>Linux x230 4.19.0-5-amd64 #1 SMP Debian 4.19.37-3 (2019-05-15) x86_64 GNU/Linux&lt;br/&gt;
Distributor ID:	Debian&lt;br/&gt;
Description:	Debian GNU/Linux 10 (buster)&lt;br/&gt;
Release:	10&lt;br/&gt;
Codename:	buster&lt;br/&gt;
</environment>
